      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">You get Speed Surge at R10 and it's pretty great. But at 22 you get Life Surge, which offers the same 5% life absorption on damage you deal with regular attacks. But instead of speeding your stamina bar up, it decreases the mob's evasion. You can only have one of these buffs active at a time on  yourself. I could keep em both and switch once the enfeeblement is on the mob, but then I'm losing either more acc or faster stamina. <br /> <br />I'm leaning towards speed surge, just because Feint tends to more than make up for accuracy problems. But with groups, I wonder if it's more beneficial to lower a mob's evasion for the other PT members. Anyone else at this point and make a decision?<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXIV: Ponce Jones (Mysidia) <br /> <br /><a href="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4055014" title="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4055014" rel="external nofollow">http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4055014</a></div></div>
