      <div class="msgContentFrame">Which to use is very situational, solo i prefer Speed Surge as it is Haste + enDrain as opposed to ACC+ and enDrain. In larger groups the reduced evasion is easily the better choice for one of the lancers, the rest should still use speed surge. I am pretty sure that the Life Surge status effect overwrites the Speed Surge one one the mob when hit (a debuff is granted on a successful hit with either up) but when switching between the two Life seems to overwrite Speed. Solo, however, the lowered evasion is pointless as your most efficient damage/tp weapon skill is usable on misses only and you should really be hoping to miss 50ish percent of the time.  <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">CamouflageNoise wrote:</div><div class="orig"> 5% life absorption on damage you deal with regular attacks.</div></div> <br /> <br />Both grant 25% damage dealt to hp drain. Hitting for 100 damge returns 25 hp everytime. <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=1980901" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=1980901"><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1748800.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></a> <br /><span class="sm"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Aripyanfar wrote:</div><div class="orig">While Manosuke is <i>not</i> a Kirby sock, we<i> can</i> blame Kirby for Manosuke.</div></div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Catt wrote:</div><div class="orig">Arathas/Manosuke... you need a better name. So I think I'm going to call you Phil.</div></div></span> <br /></div></div>
